This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a variant of multiclass logistic regression. The use of the Tsallis divergence suggests that it may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper's focus on developing a more robust algorithm suggests that it may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of iterative algorithms suggests that it may also be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper's experimental results suggest that it may also be relevant to the statistics (cs.ST) sub-category.
